&gt; You&#39;re the only person I&#39;ve heard mention this, and
&gt; it makes me feel better knowing I&#39;m not crazy (at keast
&gt; totally). lol Long ago I noticed that running tap water
&gt; sometimes seems to sound like garbled speech. I never
&gt; tested this with a recorder, but I&#39;ve caught some evps
&gt; with refrigerator motors and other devices. Audacity has
&gt; the &quot;add white noise&quot; option, which allows you to
&gt; record directly to your computer and allow the entities to
&gt; organize the generic white noise. I&#39;m eager to try
&gt; that. An excellent observation you had, Misty. I think they
&gt; must grab hold of any babbling or whirring noise available
&gt; to communicate, whether we&#39;re able to pick it up or
&gt; not. That&#39;s why I carry around one of the lightweight
&gt; Olympus recorders -- no telling where you&#39;re going to
&gt; find a babbling-brook or steady motor sound. Good ear!
